  <cite><span class="title">
  <span>IMPROVED MAGNETOOPTIC TRAPPING IN A VAPOR CELL</span>
  <i>OPTICS LETTERS</i>
</span>
<span class="authors">GIBBLE, K. E., Kasapi, S., Chu, S.</span>

<span class="details">
   <span class="year">1992</span>; <span class="volume">17 (7)</span><span class="pages">: 526-528</span>
</span></cite>
    <div class="detail">
      <h4>Abstract</h4>
  <p class="abstract">We have captured 3.6 x 10(10) cesium atoms in a magneto-optic trap loaded from a vapor cell. The 300-fold increase in the number of trapped atoms compared with that of previous research was accomplished by using larger laser intensities and 4-cm-diameter laser beams. The loading time constant was as short as 0.2 s.</p>
  <p class="wos">
    <span>View details for <a href="/https://ws.isiknowledge.com/cps/openurl/service?url_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_id=info:ut/A1992HK74400022">Web of Science ID A1992HK74400022</a></span>
